&nbsp;
The following year, O.J. Simpson was sentenced to 9 years for robbery.> His story, among others the New York Times, was a source of inspiration for books, films, studies and debates on justice, racial issues, public exposure of celebrities in a country where these themes are very felt. Today the world press recalls its history: as a poor child and with raking problems, who learned to run away from the police with the teenage bands he was part of in San Francisco, a superpaid football star. In the 1970s he was one of the most famous players in the popular U.S. sports, in the Buffalo Bills with jersey 36. He won the Heisman Trophy and was included in the Hall of Fame of professional football; appeared in dozens of films and commercials for Hertz and other customers; was a sports analyst for ABC and NBC becoming an American idol.
